txt.en: 'Guards!'
'What have I paid you weaklings for!?'
'I shall see your kind brought to ruin by the Dark Lord himself, I swear it!'
'Stop this! I'll give you anything you want! Gold! Land! Stop!'
Instance: The Riches of Rhûn
'Your people were fools to remain on the fields in the final hours of the battle - mourn them as nothing greater than that!'
'Look ahead, Jarl! A lord's tent!
'A bunch of worthless sell-swords!'
'Cowards! You should have faced your deaths on the fields!'
'You have chosen your enemies poorly, Variag!'
'We have battled through many Khundolar already, but it shall not be long before they bolster their numbers.'
'Let us go, [placeholder]!'
'Swiftly now! We must press on!'
'Zarhal Kôz must be there...but he would be a great fool to have left himself defenceless.'
'[placeholder], if we are ambushed, you must continue the fight. He cannot escape alive!'
'Out of my way, cur!'
'Clear the area! Leave none alive to aid him!'
'Die, Khundolar filth!'
'Zarhal Kôz! The time has come to repay your debts of blood and gold!'
'Honourless fool!'
'Come forth, coward, or your tent burns!'
'Your cats are hardier than you, weaklings!'
'Do not play coy, Kôz. It does not suit even one as lowly as you.'
'You have slain our brethren, broken our deal, and cheated us out of our just reward!
'You speak true - the time for mercy is done!'
'As I heard it, you deserted the battle. I robbed you of nothing but the chance to shed your dishonour in death!
'All I want is vengeance!'
'You and the rest of your Variag dogs do not deserve to kneel before my people.'
'The Blue Caste shall not forget this...'
'Gurthilm! Stop this!'
'Why have you come?'
'You failed in your task. Do not put the blame on me!'
'You were given what you deserved...a bounty of gold and what should have been a swift death upon your return.'
'I owe you no mercy, brigand. I shall send you as slaves to the pits of Udûn!
